column2: Article 17 web tool > Biogegraphical assessments at Member State level > Habitats assessment
column3:
The conservation status code indicated in the overall assessment section of the table for period 2013-2018, the country of interest and the habitat category of interest. To retrieve it: 
1) go on https://nature-art17.eionet.europa.eu/article17/habitat/report/
2) select period 2013-2018, the habitat group/category of interst (e.g. "Forest" for "woodlands and forests" in column B of the data set - tab "data") and the country of interest and click "Filter"
3) find the HABITATCODE of interest in the first column and the associated current conservation status ("Curr. CS") in the sub column "Overall assessment"
column4: drop-down menu. Note that if you cannot find the associated habitat code on the web tool, browse through the other groups - they are generally classified based on the first number of the habitat code, e.g. Costal habitats start with "1", "Rocky habitats" start with "8".

column2: Article 17 web tool > Biogegraphical assessments at Member State level > Habitats assessment
column3:
The conservation status code indicated in the overall assessment section of the table for period 2001-2006, the country of interest and the habitat category of interest. To retrieve it: 
1) go on https://nature-art17.eionet.europa.eu/article17/habitat/report/
2) select period 2001-2006, the habitat group/category of interst (e.g. "Forest" for "woodlands and forests" in column B of the data set - tab "data") and the country of interest and click "Filter"
3) find the HABITATCODE of interest in the first column and the associated current conservation status column "Overall assessment".
